nodes.bodyText: Prior to this PR, there was no integration test for creating an S3FileHandle using an existing file in S3

The object does not necessarily exist in S3 at the time the client returns from the putObject() call.  See other cases in which putObject() is called to see how we wait for the object to appear before continuing.
either (1) replace 'Exception' with the particular exception type thrown by 'getObject' or (2) ensure that only the getObject() method invocation is within the try/catch block.
the constant "/externalFileHandle/googleCloud" should be defined in a file (URLHelpers.java??)
